2. cs.COMM (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper proposes a communication system that can be applied to wireless networks, making this category a likely fit. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a system that combines different coding techniques to improve the performance of a communication system, which can be seen as a control problem. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper proposes a communication system that can be used to transmit multimedia data, making this category a possible fit. 
5. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper proposes a communication system that can be applied to networked systems, making this category a possible fit.
